Human Resources Officer
29 Apr 2014 08:39 PM - UAE
. Emaar Hospitality owns and manages a diverse and award-winning portfolio of hospitality assets including Hotels, Serviced Residences, Golf Resorts, a Polo and Equestrian club, Health Clubs, the Dubai Marina and associated Yacht Club. The Address Hotel & Resorts operates a number of luxurious Angsana Spas within these leisure complexes. In addition, Emaar Hospitality has launched mall based stand-alone restaurant concepts.   We are currently looking for a Human Resources Officer to join our dynamic HR Team at our Leisure Division handling the HR Operations of Arabian Ranches Golf Club & Dubai Polo and Equestrian Club. Mainly responsible for providing support in the various human resources functions, which include administration, employee welfare activities, recruitment, payroll and employee coaching & counselling. Suitable candidate should be a graduate in Human Resources with a minimum of 2 years of experience in a similar role. Key Responsiblities: Ensure an effective Human Resources administration including reports and statistics Ensure the Personnel files and employee records are accurate and up to date Prepare all final Settlements in conjunction with the Payroll Officer Maintain an accurate plan of all recruitment requirements for vacancies within the Business unit as agreed with the Department heads and HR Manager. Maintain an accurate record of all planned promotions / Increments/transfers Establish a network of contacts / list of potential candidates through regular speculative recruitment and pass all relevant details to the Recruitment team regarding all recruitment activity and potential candidates to remain on file for future consideration Proactively ensure that visas are obtained by the PRO for all new and existing employees within agreed service levels and set timescales. Make offers of employment to potential candidates that are in line with budgets, headcount plans, salary scales and HR policies and procedures. Monitor and support all new employees joining the business to ensure they arrive within the required timescales Support Department heads/Managers to ensure all new employees receive a comprehensive induction/welcome to the property. Actively participate in organizing various events for Associates such as Annual Staff Party, Employee Recognition, General Sessions, Birthday Celebrations, Team Outing etc.  Ensure that the standards required by Law and by Management are maintained at all times in all Human Resources related areas. Personal Profile & Essential Skills: Displays emotional maturity and sensitivity in dealing with others. Operates with integrity and objectivity at all times Organised and demonstrates good planning skills Proactive to address and resolve issues. Ability to work and deliver results in a fast paced work environment A Team player. Should have excellent grooming standards First class people skills and the ability to communicate effectively across a multi-national, multi-cultural environment. Fluent in spoken and written English Should be excellent in using various computer packages - Word, Excel, PowerPoint and H (more...)
